                        <h3><li>Booking a Pick-C Trip</li></h3>
                        <b></li>2.1 Enable Location Services<br /></li></b>
                        <br />
                        Prior to accessing the Pick-C mobile app, you must enable the GPS location of your mobile, which helps the app to automatically select the pickup location.
                        <br />
                        You can turn on the location by doing either of the following ways:
                        </li>
                        <br />
                        <br />
                        <ul>
                            <li>Up on logging in to Pick-C app without enabling the GPS, it will notify you to enable the location services.</li>
                            <li>
                                In your mobile phone go to settings, tap Location and tap Location on button.<br />
                                Once the location is turned on you can start the booking process.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <br />
                        <b></li>2.2	Providing a Pickup Address<br /></li></b>
                        <p>To provide a pickup address for Pick-C, make sure that you have entered the correct pickup address before booking the truck. Ensure that your GPS Location is turned on, so that the app automatically sets the pickup location. You can view your location in the map on your mobile screen with a flag pointing on your location. You can set a pickup location by either ways:</p>

                        <ul>
                            <li>Place the flag to you required location</li>
                            <li>You can manually type the location in the Pickup Location field <br /><br /><img src="~/images/helpImages/book.png" alt="booking image"></li>
                            <p>After pickup location is set, tap on the lock location <img src="~/images/helpImages/lock-location-btn.png" alt="location lock button" style="width:75px; vertical-align: middle;">  icon to lock the pickup location, so that if you accidently place the flag on some other location the pickup location will not change. If you are unable to find your current location in the map, tap on My Location <img src="~/images/helpImages/location-icon.png" alt="location lock button" style="width:30px; vertical-align: middle;"> button on the map.  </p>
                            <p><b>Note:</b>Once the booking is confirmed, you cannot change your pickup location, so make sure you have entered correct pickup address.</p>

                        </ul>
                        <br />
                        <b></li>2.3	Providing a Drop Address<br /></li></b>
                        <p>Entering a drop location helps the driver to find the right navigation to your destination without any trouble.</p>
                        <p><b>Note:</b> Once the drop location is locked, only then you can book a truck. It is mandatory to enter your drop location before you book a truck.</p>
                        <p>You can enter a drop location by doing either of the following:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Selecting the drop location by tapping on the drop location field, and manually entering</li>
                            <li>Moving the flag to your drop location in the map which is provided on your screen </li>
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <li class="list-style-none"><img src="~/images/helpImages/drop-location.png" alt="drop location image" /></li>
                            <br />

                            <p>Once you lock the drop location you can’t move the flag to other location. To change the drop location you must tap on the lock location <img src="~/images/helpImages/lock-location-btn.png" alt="location lock button" style="width:75px; vertical-align: middle;"> icon to unlock the drop location, which is available above the flag, and move the flag to your desired location.</p>
                        </ul>

